article.description: Andre Spight, Jalen Sanders and Jordan Davis combined to score 70 points and Northern Colorado routed Northern Arizona, 95-60 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Northern Colorado trio score 70, rout Northern Arizona 95-60
article.linkText: Northern Colorado trio score 70, rout Northern Arizona 95-60
article.story: GREELEY, Colo. -- Andre Spight, Jalen Sanders and Jordan Davis combined to score 70 points and Northern Colorado routed Northern Arizona, 95-60 on Thursday night. The Bears held a seven-point lead at intermission, but outscored the Lumberjacks by 28 over the final 20 minutes. Spight hit 4 of 7 from distance and finished 25 points to lead the Bears. Sanders hit 8 of 10 from the field and totaled 24 points while Davis converted 9 of 10 form the floor to amass 21 points. Northern Colorado (17-10, 8-6) finished the game shooting 59.2 percent, hitting 32 of 54 shots, including 10 of 24 from beyond the 3-point arc. Northern Arizona (4-22, 1-12) got 15 points from Jojo Anderson and 13 each from Karl Harris and Corey Brown. The Lumberjacks shot 21 of 60 (35 percent), hitting just 2 of 16 from distance.
